    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/battlestars-daybreak-worst-ending-history-screen-science-fiction#comment-10014" class="active">Have to agree</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by CoreKnell (not verified) on Tue, 2009-07-14 11:37.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I have to agree wholeheartedly.  The whole "God did it" answer probably wouldn't have stung quite so much -- even though it is still a lame copout -- if it hadn't directly contradicted the entire presentation of the show. Pretty brazen to show "... and they have a plan" at the beginning over every episode when they so clearly did not.  Also to tack one of those "all will be revealed" slogans to every promo ("You will know the truth", "The truth will be revealed", etc.) when they clearly had no intention of ever revealing anything.</p>
<p>As mentioned, the fall was so great only because they had previously achieved such great heights.</p>
