    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/battlestars-daybreak-worst-ending-history-screen-science-fiction#comment-10025" class="active">I&#039;m surprised more people</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Anonymous (not verified) on Tue, 2009-07-14 13:22.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I'm surprised more people aren't calling Moore out on Apollo's "We've given them their freedom, they've earned it line." You don't earn freedom. It's a fundamental right. I feel that Moore totally missed the point when he had characters that look like us, have emotions, are intelligent and we still deprive them of fundamental human rights. Instead of taking on the African/Cylon analogy -they don't look like us, so it's okay to oppress them- he perpetrated it.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; </div>
